	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64605865">Been tutoring all age groups for a couple decades. First fail is, considering the huge variety of individuals, there is no monolithic curriculum, and as a student progresses, it also changes. Second, as humans walking around in the world, we already innately do all sort of very complex math without noticing, just nobody has every put a label on it for us. Third is discover the compelling application that can provide metaphors for the math involved, like cooking, athletics, music, whatever. Fourth is realizi</div>
